I've told myself every year that I'd do it- learn or get an accountant but it's always pushed to next.  I'd like to change that this year, just somehow

It's a lonely experience, at least for me 😐

I'm entering my 30's and just now starting to learn legal stuff better- learning investing was a big bonus for me this year.  

I just for the love of god- want to know what I'm doing.  My mind isn't organized- what takes one person to do tasks like this in minutes takes me hours

when I look into tax software- the problem seems to amplify- I've been doing everything by the old fashioned book since 2013.  I want an accountant but I don't know who to go to- what information to present.   It's scary.
at the very least- whatever numbers I put in I can at least try to make the math right with them.  But it's scary- will I get a bad letter this year?  Next year?

I want to grow- but i obviously need an accountant or at least a good lesson on how to even keep track of anything.  Between E*sy and cons- I'm always worried I'm picking and crunching the wrong numbers-

Every single year around this time, I get terrified.  Because, when I'm ready to do my taxes and go into self employment, I have absolutely no idea what I'm doing- what numbers are right wrong.  What's worse is, I really don't even know where to start.
